> <OLD>
>
> WHEELIE would meet GRIMLOCK or be crushed trying.  An often enough
> circumstance.
>
> Glancing up at TERRANOTRON, "Me think that you should go.  He's my friend, I
> hope I know.  If I am the one who gets caught, for my sake you should not
> waste your own for naught."
>
> Calling out again, boosting his vocalizer after he had given the Maximal who
> had warned him away, "Me Wheelie Say Find Friends Today!"  Letting it be
> known who he was, his vocalizer booming to announce his presence, for better
> or for worse now, waiting at the end of the bridge.

<NEW>

TERRANOTRON shrugged, "Watch your tail." he said quietly as he flapped
his wings and launched himself into the air. "Something is controlling
him, friend of no friend you are in danger." As moved upwards he
pointed at the bridge, "if you need to run across it."

As the avian DINOBOT moved away GRIMLOCK burst through the foliage,
practically knocking small trees aside and ripping up brush. He might
be in a smaller form now that he, like so many others had reduced
their size across the centuries, but he was still strong and mighty
and a true force to be reckoned with.

As GRIMLOCK's 12' tall superbly armored Tyrannosaurus form made it
self visible he roared, the report of it echoing through the trees and
skyward. Birds flittered from the upper branches as animals scattered.

"Who dares be a friend of Grimlock?!" GRIMLOCK bellowed as he looked
down at WHEELIE, his large jaws almost salivating. There was a crazed
look in his optics as his smaller arms flexed their hands. He may have
looked like the old GRIMLOCK, but he certainly wasn't acting quite
like him.

Behind GRIMLOCK SNARL, SLUDGE and SLAG were no doubt making their
approach from the sounds coming from the brush.

(TAG)

- Preston
